-- Thunder Beat Lakers, Bulls Defeat Cavaliers in First Round of NBA Playoffs
-- Nancy Kercheval
-- 2010-04-23T05:19:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/thunder-beat-lakers-bulls-defeat-cavaliers-in-first-round-of-nba-playoffs.html

          
          
             Kevin Durant scored 29 points
and had 19 rebounds to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a
101-96 win over the defending champion Los Angeles Lakers
in round one of the National Basketball Association
playoffs.  
 Russell Westbrook added 27 points as the Thunder
closed within 2-1 in the series with the victory at Ford
Center in Oklahoma City.  
 Kobe Bryant led the Lakers with 24 points.  
 The Chicago Bulls secured a 108-106 win over the
Cavaliers when Clevelandâ€™s Anthony Parker missed from 42
feet at the buzzer at the United Center in Chicago.  
 Derrick Rose scored 31 points and Kirk Hinrich added
27 for the Bulls, who trail 2-1 in the best-of-seven
series.  
 LeBron James had 39 points for Cleveland.  
 At the Rose Garden in Portland, Oregon, the Phoenix
Suns took a 2-1 series lead with a 108-89 win over the
Portland Trail Blazers.  
 Jason Richardson had 42 points for the Suns. LaMarcus
Aldridge scored 17 while Martell Webster and Jerryd Bayless
came off the bench to add 14 points each for the Trail
Blazers.  
